h Handlungsstrategien bei Lernwiderständen, Lernvermeiden bzw. Nicht-Lernen in den Blick.  aLearning strategies are frequently discussed. But when does content become relevant for the learner themselves? This critical-pragmatic study inverts the focus and opens up new perspectives for overcoming learning barriers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aAdult education. 0aAdult learning. 0aOnline social networksxSociological aspects. 4aBildung. 4aBildungsforschung. 4aBildungsgeschichte. 4aBildungstheorie. 4aBiographie. 4aEmpirische Methoden. 4aErwachsene. 4aPädagogik. 7aEDUCATION / Philosophy, Theory & Social Aspects.2bisacsh  aAdults.  aBiography.  aEducation.  aEducational Research.  aEmpirical Methods.  aHistory of Education.  aPedagogy.  aTheory of Education.1 aBracker, Rosa, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2015z9783110438741oZDB-23-DSW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783839430958zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839430958423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839430958/original  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2015  aZDB-23-DSWb2015  aZDB-23-TGPc2014d2016